{"type":"message","id":"dea6235e","parentId":"9f2b0f43","timestamp":"2026-03-02T06:17:34.974Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-02 06:17 UTC] 9ers0n ŌĆö 11:42 onboard this channel qubit APP ŌĆö 11:43 I can help set up this channel! To make sure I configure it right, what kind of onboarding are you looking for? Options: Intro message ŌĆö I can introduce myself (Qubit) to the channel and explain what I can help with Task tracking ŌĆö Set up this channel for task management like the #task-management channel Custom workflow ŌĆö Configure specific automations, notifications, or workflows for #acutis-flow Something else ŌĆö Tell me what you have in mind What would be most useful for this channel? ­¤żö Reacted to your message while waiting to hear what kind of onboarding you'd like for #acutis-flow. --- see the above discord channel onboarding xp. not good. too complex. expecting a simple \"What is this channel about?\" question."}],"timestamp":1772432254972}}
{"type":"message","id":"7a5fa9fd","parentId":"dea6235e","timestamp":"2026-03-02T06:17:47.544Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is showing me an example of what they consider a bad onboarding experience - it's too complex with multiple options and formal structure. They want something simpler: just asking \"What is this channel about?\" \n\nThis is feedback about how I should approach channel onboarding in the future. They want a simpler, more natural approach. I should acknowledge this and note it for future reference.\n\nI should check if there's a relevant skill for Discord operations, and also update my memory about this preference.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"You're rightŌĆöthat's overengineered. A simple question beats a multiple-choice menu every time.\n\nLet me save this preference so I don't repeat it:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_836cd535db7c4ffeae983972","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"memory/2026-03-02.md","content":"# 2026-03-02\n\n## Channel Onboarding - Preference Noted\n\nGerson wants a **simple onboarding approach** for Discord channels:\n- ŌØī Bad: Multiple choice menus, formal options, complex workflows\n- Ō£ģ Good: Just ask \"What is this channel about?\"\n\nKeep it conversational, not bureaucratic.\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":216,"output":225,"cacheRead":12992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13433,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772432254973}}
